jobPositions.title: Junior Front-end Developer
jobPositions.description:
A well-established AI governance platform that serves customer interests with responsible algorithms is looking for a Junior Front-End Developer. The developer will be in charge of developing a highly interactive and customizable front-end for the AI validation and governance platform. The company helps organizations to attain a higher purpose with responsible AI that benefits people. The company has managed to raise funds worth $1 mn+ during their pre-seed round. This role will be a long-term, full-time opportunity requiring some overlap with the EST/IST time zones.
 Job Requirements: • Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Engineering, Computer Science (or equivalent experience) • At least 2+ years of experience as a front-end developer • Prolific experience working with JavaScript frameworks such as React • Experience working with JavaScript plotting tools like D3 • Profound skills Computer Science concepts, design principles, and data structures • Prior understanding of CI/CD tools such as Jenkins, GitLab is nice to have • Familiarity with Typescript and Python is desirable • Nice to have some experience with AI/Machine learning products • Proactive interest and experience in aesthetic designs • Excellent attention to detail and collaboration skills
jobPositions.responsibility: Job Responsibilities: • Implement various analytical dashboards, including the UI for scalable AI monitoring • Collaborate with product managers and designers to deliver quality products • Continuously drive initiatives and improvements on the front-end engineering, UI/UX design, and brand contributions • Add new features and scale the existing services • Build scalable, responsive, and well-documented stacks

jobPositions.title: Junior Angular Developer
jobPositions.description:
Job highlights
Qualifications
•
You should have a penchant for excellence with a proven track-record of successfully delivering high quality work, be a lifelong learner, have a positive attitude, be self-motivated, and have excellent English skills
•
To be successful in this role, you should have experience using server-side logic and work well in a team
•
Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience)
•
3+ years of experience working with Angular (rare exceptions for highly skilled candidates)
•
Proficient in HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript
•
Write clean, efficient, and well-optimized code
•
Good knowledge of JavaScript MV-VM/MVC frameworks including Angular
•
Work with other developers to maintain workflow and integrate various components
•
Build compelling web applications using best practices of the AngularJS framework
•
Experience in writing cross-browser compatible code
•
Experience using JavaScript building tools (like Gulp, Grunt, etc.)
•
Working knowledge of database, APIs, proxies, caching layer, and other web services
•
Familiarity with RESTful services
•
Familiarity with back-end programming languages such as Java, .NET, Python, Ruby, etc
•
Working knowledge of technologies such as AJAX and DOM manipulation techniques
•
Capability to implement AngularJS applications, directives, controllers, and services
•
Experience with testing frameworks (e.g., Mocha, Jasmine, etc.)
•
Working knowledge of test runner tools (e.g., Karma, JEST, etc.)
•
Strong knowledge of source control systems (Git, Merging, Branching, Pull Requests, etc.)

Job description
Overview: Remote Angular Developer Company Description: Cosmogence is a platform that provides remote Angular Developer jobs that allow you to work from anywhere for companies in Canada and the United States. Cosmogence is looking to fill remote Angular Developer jobs for our clients who are interested in hiring remote, full-time employees from around the world to be a part of their team. You should have a penchant for excellence with a proven track-record of successfully delivering high quality work, be a lifelong learner, have a positive attitude, be self-motivated, and have excellent English skills. The specific tools and technologies, years of experience and job requirements will vary depending on the client you are hired by, so we are open to a variety of skill types and levels of experience. We’re looking for the best of the best–if you think that’s you, we encourage you to apply! Once you submit your profile, you will undergo our vetting process, and will be considered for a variety of clients. We will match you based on your interests, desired compensation, and their needs. Job Description: As an Angular Developer, you will be responsible to write and test code, debugging programs and integrating applications with third-party web services. To be successful in this role, you should have experience using server-side logic and work well in a team. You will be a part of a creative team that is responsible for all aspects of the ongoing application development from the initial specification, through to developing, bug fix and launching. Required Skills: • Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience) • 3+ years of experience working with Angular (rare exceptions for highly skilled candidates) • Proficient in HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript • Write clean, efficient, and well-optimized code • Good knowledge of JavaScript MV-VM/MVC frameworks including Angular • Work with other developers to maintain workflow and integrate various components • Build compelling web applications using best practices of the AngularJS framework • Experience in writing cross-browser compatible code • Experience using JavaScript building tools (like Gulp, Grunt, etc.) • Working knowledge of database, APIs, proxies, caching layer, and other web services • Familiarity with RESTful services • Familiarity with back-end programming languages such as Java, .NET, Python, Ruby, etc. • Working knowledge of technologies such as AJAX and DOM manipulation techniques • Capability to implement AngularJS applications, directives, controllers, and services Nice to have: • Experience with testing frameworks (e.g., Mocha, Jasmine, etc.) • Working knowledge of test runner tools (e.g., Karma, JEST, etc.) • Strong knowledge of source control systems (Git, Merging, Branching, Pull Requests, etc

jobPositions.title: Full Stack MEAN Engineer
jobPositions.description: A fast-emerging start-up building tools to improve code quality is looking for a Full-stack MERN Engineer. The engineer will be responsible for developing and implementing consistent custom development solutions for the applications and technologies. The company has developed solutions that offer comprehensive reports evaluating the quality of code, security, and third-party IP risks. Candidates who would like to build solutions with great impact and grow rapidly in their careers are suitable for this role. It requires a minimum of 4+ hours overlap with EST. Job Responsibilities: • Develop medium to large scale software projects • Analyze, interpret and make decisions affecting work methods and procedures • Participate in requirements analysis and architectural design • Write detailed, accurate, and concise development documentation • Debug and resolve complex software problems in existing software
jobPositions.responsibility: Job Requirements: • Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience) • Must be experienced with the MERN stack, including MongoDB, Express, React, and Node • Solid understanding of building scalable web APIs • Experience architecting high impact, reliable applications with a responsive design • Familiarity with writing code that works on multiple platforms and browsers • Ability to articulate and communicate effectively • Strong desire to stay up-to-date on current technologies and suggest areas of improvement
